docs.abstract: Technology was once used at big corporate events just to let you sign in or see the agenda. Now, it can record who you met, and for how long.
docs.snippet: Technology was once used at big corporate events just to let you sign in or see the agenda. Now, it can record who you met, and for how long.
docs.lead_paragraph: The corporate event has gone digital. Paper tickets and itineraries have given way to badge swipes and electronic agendas. Chance meetings have been replaced by automatically curated networking. And there’s no need to take notes for colleagues who can’t be there — they can watch a live stream of the event and use their phones to submit questions.

headline.main: My Wrist Is Glowing: At Business Events, Shorter Lines and Less Privacy
headline.print_headline: Making Old-Fashioned Connections the Newfangled Way

docs.lead_paragraph: LOS ANGELES — The most unpopular move the Academy of Motion Picture Arts and Sciences may have ever made was reversed on Thursday: The next Academy Awards will not add a category for achievement in “popular” films after all.

headline.main: New ‘Popular’ Oscar Scrapped by Film Academy for 2019
headline.print_headline: ‘Popular’ Oscar Award Is Scrapped by Academy
